    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 996.2 Carrera, featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant delivering linear torque through a precise 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. This example features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement, addressing critical failure points for peace of mind. The chassis retains its signature communicative feedback via a well-maintained McPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension setup. Equipped with staggered alloys and four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers, the braking performance remains sharp and fade-resistant. While the aesthetic reflects honest road use, the drivetrain remains tight, and the engine pulls strongly to redline with no bore scoring symptoms. A driver-spec machine optimized for the purist.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 48
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_3",
